OL,3,CFormer Tory leader warns of
OL,4,Cexistential threat if party fails to
OL,5,Cpull together
OL,7,F"He is one of the hardest working
OL,8,Findividuals I've ever come across in
OL,9,Fpolitics and his own personal
OL,10,Fdiscipline makes that easier - he
OL,11,Fdoesn't drink and he doesn't eat that
OL,12,Fmuch.
OL,14,F"The result is a high energy level all
OL,15,Fthe time. Most people, you know, have
OL,16,Fa big lunch, slow down a bit in the
OL,17,Fafternoon, have their big dinner sleep
OL,18,Fit off. But Rishi his energy level is
OL,19,Flike this," added Hague raising his
OL,20,Fhand in the air. "There's no slump. He
OL,21,Fjust keeps going all the time."
